    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Domestic spaces, sometimes windowless, primarily designed or used to hold home entertainment systems as their focus, especially for viewing and listening to prerecorded or computer-based materials, such as videos, music, or games. For domestic spaces designed for high-end audio-video equipment to simulate a theaterlike environment, use "home theaters."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
